title: clean up and successful videoroom test
message:
clean up and successful videoroom test

I have successfully tested the videoroom plugin with this API. The feed
to the browser is a little choppy and trickling MUST be set to true, but
it's a start

Also did some clean as suggested by android lent, to clean up the
visible API interactions

title: Echotest plugin now works
message:
Echotest plugin now works

The issue was that callbacks were being handled in the UI thread...all
of them. So there were lockups... Better asynchronous logic is still
needed and some sanity checks and cleanup

title: Testable for Echotest
message:
Testable for Echotest

Everything worked just fine for the echotest but, for some reason the
mediastream is not giving any media. or at least it is not playing.

On remote stream is being fired as designed, and the display updates but
there is no stream being decoded and painted to the screen

title: Handling trickling better
message:
Handling trickling better

Corrected trickling logic so that it does not wait for a null
candidate(which does not happen natively) and fires events on
IceGathering Complete status.

Some of it is actually working :)

title: moved away from java_websocket
message:
moved away from java_websocket

Moved to AndroidAsync and away from java_websocket. Just could not get
any information on sub-protocols for java_websocket and the asynchronous
nature of AndroidAsync may prove to be a better fit in the future
anyways(It also supports plane HTTP requests for the Janus Rest
interface).

title: Corrected Websocket Draft
message:
Corrected Websocket Draft

Alright, websocket draft works at Draft_17, however the sub protocol
still seems to be incorrect...not sure how to set it in this websocket
client

title: Numerous items...original I know
message:
Numerous items...original I know

Removed unneeded dependencies to jackson, changed build a bit, changed
the manifest and the activity.

Right now, websocket connection fails with a close -1 as the
reason...could be that the sub-protocol is not being set or it is the
wrong draft.
